Dear Mr Girin,

Sorry for my late feedback. 
First, I would like to thank you for the quality of your offer and for the time spend on it. 

Following Internal review with Project team please find here under conclusion of our meeting on your offer. 

•	Quality wise, the Compliance matrix had no critical point. 
Therefore, rating is Green 

•	Purchasing wise : you are average. 
Offer still seems clear for our R&D and commercially it is comparable with others offers.
Therefore, Rating is, purchasing wise, Orange. 

•	Financial and company size:  only 20-49 employees : Difficult to face any project timing change due to resources constrains in case of problem. 
Therefore, rating is Orange

•	R&D wise : Offer is feting to our need, and we thank you for the support and guidance provided during this RFQ  
Nevertheless, fact that you are using exclusively one tool provider is seen from our side as additional risk and we noted that you propose to use  tools  aligned  with our
  usage but it is still a risk that we don’t have with the other design houses. 
Therefore, rating is Yellow/Green

•	Industrialization : 
Good Level for industrialization but we  don’t  feel the same  proactivity in  the  proposal.

Due to time constrains we need to select 2 Design houses to continue our RFQ.
Due to the overall rating we didn’t selected IC Alps for the next step. 

Based on the other criteria assessed, we would like to highlight the fact that we consider ICAlps as a legitimate candidate for further investigation and RFQ and will surely quote again for other projects. 

I’ll be out of office for the next two weeks but If you have any questions, please feel free to ask or to call me when I come back on 5th of October . 

Best regards,                                                                                     

Pierre Endres
Purchasing Commodity Leader

Comme discuté il y a quelques semaines, nous avons besoin d'un circuit de mesure du signal cardiaque sous-cutané et nous explorons la possibilité de nous fournir à l'extérieur de Microport.
Voici quelques informations pour cadrer notre besoin et démarrer un échange :
•	Filtrage préalable : passe-bande 0.05 Hz ou 1 Hz à 128 Hz.
•	Niveau de signal min : 100 uV pic
•	Niveau de signal max : 5 mV pic
•	Niveau de bruit ramené à l'entrée : 10 uV pic.
•	Gain 255 (à discuter)
•	Signal unipolaire ou différentiel
•	Consommation : 0.5 uA max, moins si possible.
 
La fonctionnalité complète comprendra un ADC et un filtrage numérique pour finaliser la mise en forme du signal. 
Je vous propose d'entamer la discussion sur cette base et de confronter ces éléments de spécification aux IP dont vous disposez déjà.

• Master SPI, compliant with SPI JESD68.01, 
• Master Dump.
